title: For Sale:  Consistent Cartidge Crimp
postcontent:
The Consistent Crimp


    * Produces quantifiable crimp pressure in Foot Pounds
    * Makes specific crimp pressures repeatable load after load
    * Allows you to return to any specific crimp pressure even after die adjustment or die swap.
    * Saves you money
    * If you are not using our Consistent Crimp- you are just guessing.


            Consistency is Accuracy


            The problem. : How do we answer the questions we have all been asking:
            How much crimp is a good crimp?
            How do I crimp my bullets?
            How Do I crimp my brass?
            Is there a secret correct cartridge reloading crimp?


            The above similar questions can be distilled to one question, "What is a good brass to bullet crimp?" However as soon as we ask this question we jump to the next question, "if the correct crimp is discovered, how does one repeat this bullet crimp each time one returns to this load recipe, makes a die adjustment or even a die swap?" Put in other words, "What is the secret to finding the best crimp and consistently repeating this brass to bullet crimp?"


            We've all been there, we've spent the money for the tools and components, we've spent the time preparing the cases, made careful powder and bullet selection and then for the final step we are told to "put a good crimp on it." . Everything else is meticulously measured and consistent so why shouldn't the same emphasis be placed on the crimp?


            The solution: The Consistent Crimp

            What is it?

            The Consistent Crimp is a specifically designed Micro-Click torque wrench with a patent pending adapter that enables the Consistent Crimp to be attached to to a single stage reloading press, instantly converting the press into a calibrated measuring device. When joined these two tools become more than their separate parts enabling the reloader to quantify the amount of crimp pressure being applied to form a crimp.

            How it works?

            The Consistent Crimp allows the reloader to select and repeat specific crimp pressures in foot pounds, for any given load. The reloader simply selects the desired amount of crimp pressure by setting the Micro Click Torque wrench and using the Consistent Crimp as the press handle during the crimping operation. The Micro Click torque wrench alerts the reloader both audibly and by "feel" when the desired crimp pressure has been reached. The Consistent Crimp can be set in as little as .2 FtPd increments!

            Some of the benefits

            The Consistent Crimp allows the reloader to eliminate the guessing game of "How much crimp?" or "What is a good crimp" in several ways:


                + Quantifies the input pressure: The Consistent Crimp measures the input pressure being applied during the crimping process. This means the reloader can select the an exact amount of input pressure, test for results and return to the reloading bench to either repeat a successful crimp pressure or systematically alter the amount of crimp until the desired results have been achieved.
                + Improves Accuracy, the reloader is able to "move the groups around the face of the target" by altering the crimp.Yes, you will be astonished to watch your group average Point of Impact "move" across and around the target face as you alter the crimp pressure
                + Improves Precision, the reloader is able to reduce the size of the groups for a given load by altering the crimp pressure and by repeating the exact same crimp pressure for each bullet made in a given product run.
                  The Consistent Crimp allows the reloader to repeat or return to an exact crimp pressure even after switching or adjusting dies.
                + Determines the right amount of crimp pressure that will hold the bullet in place under recoil forces for any given load.
                + Saves you money because you can systematically discover the best crimp pressure for your favorite load.
                + Saves you money because you can return to the correct crimp pressure even after a die swap


                        In summary, just as different bullets or powder change the Point of Impact at the range so variances in crimp pressure change the Point of Impact. The Consistent Crimp enables the reloader to discover what crimp is best for a given load and gun and to return to this crimp at will. Whether you roll crimp or taper crimp or use the Lee Factory crimp dies, the Consistent crimp will dramatically improve your results.
